title: Malcolm Gladwell and friends deregulated monopoly.
pid: 653d6668-c8ca-4a75-bec2-52de89886aa1
body: |2-
  You start with a dollar.
  You buy cautiously, not taking on too much at once.
  Contracts were enforcible (i.e. binding contracts were feasible) I think.
